# Testing & Verification Policy

## Build gates

Every change must pass before being considered done:

1. **`pnpm build`** — Next.js production build must succeed
2. **TypeScript** — no type errors (`tsc --noEmit` or build catches them)
3. **Lint** — if ESLint is configured, `pnpm lint` must pass

## Verification checklist

### For collection/global/block changes
- [ ] Schema compiles without errors
- [ ] Seed script runs successfully and is idempotent
- [ ] Admin panel shows the collection/global correctly
- [ ] Fields render in admin with correct types (text, upload, select, etc.)
- [ ] Localized fields show locale switcher in admin

### For frontend changes
- [ ] Page renders without errors in dev mode
- [ ] Page renders at mobile breakpoint (375px)
- [ ] Page renders at desktop breakpoint (1440px)
- [ ] Images load correctly (from S3 or fallback)
- [ ] Locale switching works (if applicable)
- [ ] Navigation and links work
- [ ] No console errors in browser

### For seed scripts
- [ ] First run populates data correctly
- [ ] Second run does not duplicate data
- [ ] Media assets upload successfully
- [ ] Relationships between collections are correct

## What we don't have yet (and that's OK)

- No unit test framework is set up
- No E2E test framework is set up
- No CI pipeline yet

When tests are introduced, prefer:
- **Vitest** for unit/integration tests
- **Playwright** for E2E tests
- Tests for seed scripts (verify they don't throw)
- Tests for data access functions

## Visual verification

Since this is a highly visual site with cinematic effects:
- Always check the actual rendered page after changes
- Verify cinematic effects (grain, cinema depth, lens) still work
- Verify reveal animations trigger on scroll
- Verify black-and-white to color transitions on hover
- Check responsive behavior on at least mobile and desktop
